# Governance

`<repo-name>` is maintainer-led.

## Maintainers

Maintainers are responsible for:

- repository direction and scope
- review and acceptance of contributions
- protecting clarity across package docs, governance files, and GitHub-facing
  collaboration surfaces

## Decision Making

- Small changes can be proposed directly in pull requests.
- Larger changes that affect public repository shape, contributor experience,
  or governance expectations should be proposed in an issue first.
- Maintainers make final decisions when tradeoffs or scope questions remain.

## Change Expectations

Prefer small, explicit changes. When a change affects multiple parts of the
repository, call out the impact clearly in the issue or pull request.
